response:
 Here we have $6\times 6 = 36$ points.  So there are $\binom{36}{2} = 630$ line i.e. non square rectangles.  All together there are $\binom{36}{4} = 58914$ quadrilaterals.  A square rectangle is made up of two pairs of perpendicular sides, so we want to subtract off the number of rectangles that include these pairs of sides.  For example, consider the following:

[asy]draw((0,0)--(6,0)--(6,6)--(0,6)--cycle);
draw((1,5)--(6,5));
draw((5,0)--(5,6));
draw((0,1)--(6,1));
draw((1,0)--(1,6));

[/asy]

There are 9 different positions from which to select the missing square, times 16 different squares, times 2 orientations.  So $\text{Number of square rectangles} = 9\cdot 16\cdot2 = 288$.  So we subtract this from the previous count, and get the answer \boxed{58626} rectangles.*

